# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __delitem__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__delitem__')
#
# All 14 asyncio classes return false for __delitem__.
# No asyncio type exposes item deletion via del obj[key].
# asyncio primitives are terminated/cleaned up through explicit calls:
#   Task.cancel(), Future.cancel(), Handle.cancel(), StreamWriter.close().
# Queue items are consumed via get()/get_nowait(); there is no delete-by-key.
# Semaphore/Lock/Condition: resource guards with no mapping protocol at all.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

