# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __contains__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__contains__')
#
# All 14 asyncio classes return false for __contains__.
# None define membership testing via `in`.
# asyncio.Queue does not support `item in queue` — items are either retrieved
#   via get() or counted via qsize(); no membership test is offered.
# asyncio.Semaphore tracks an internal counter; `item in semaphore` is
#   meaningless and not implemented.
# asyncio.Condition, Lock, BoundedSemaphore: guards on a mutex; no `in`.
# asyncio.Handle/TimerHandle: handle objects for callbacks; no membership.
# asyncio.Timeout/TaskGroup: async context objects; no membership test.
# asyncio.StreamReader/StreamWriter: byte-stream pipes; `in` not defined.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

