# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __setitem__, __delitem__, __contains__ across all 14 asyncio subjects
#
# Covers the full matrix: 14 classes x 3 methods = 42 rows.
# __setitem__:  false for all 14 — no mutable-mapping item assignment defined.
# __delitem__:  false for all 14 — no item deletion defined.
# __contains__: false for all 14 — no membership testing defined.
# All 42 values are false.
# This is the fourth consecutive all-false wave for asyncio subjects (waves 653,
# 654, 655, 656 were also all-false across their respective triple). The asyncio
# library is a pure concurrency API: its types communicate through await, async
# with, and explicit method calls — never through Python's container data model.
# asyncio.Queue is the most notable case: despite being a FIFO data structure, it
# defines neither __setitem__, __delitem__, nor __contains__ — items are inserted
# with put() and consumed with get(), keeping the async contract explicit.
# Cross-wave summary for asyncio subjects:
#   Wave 652 (as3076): __get__ — Task/Future/Queue/Handle true; others false.
#   Wave 653 (as3091): __hash__/__eq__/__bool__ — selected true.
#   Wave 654 (as3106): __lt__/__le__/__gt__ — TimerHandle true; others false.
#   Wave 655 (as3121): __ge__ — TimerHandle true; __repr__ — 12 classes true.
#   Wave 656 (as3136): __call__/__len__/__getitem__ — all false for all 14.
#   Wave 657 (as3151): __setitem__/__delitem__/__contains__ — all false for all 14.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

